<br>
1.  This will be mentioned time and again but this is a risk you take in these types of trades.  You gave a person you have known for all of 15 minutes a substantial amount of platinum and it is naive to assume that their word is their bond based on that limited interaction.  Like most scam artists, he acted in a way (in this case, offering to call you) that would lower your defenses.  You gut suckered.  You seem to understand it was a risk you took and no use lecturing you.  <br>
<br>
2.  That is about the shittiest thing you can do to someone.  I saw Dirfrops in BoT yesterday LFG and, if what you say is true, I am not grouping with him or helping him ever.  I think Difrops is ebayed and the person that did this to you is probably not the original PoDirfrops.  Hell, it makes you wonder if PoKajinn bought Dirfrops.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessage?topicID=3788.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...3788.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
3.  First you say:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Anyway, Dirfrops did something that other players in the past had not offered to do - he offered to call me on the phone and talk one-on-one to ensure confidence in the trade. Immediately I agreed and he called.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Then you say:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You will be held accountable for what you've done. No - it may not be by me, because I didn't get your RL information.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you are serious about wanting to prevent this from happening again, you *can* help stop this.  If he called you, your phone company should have a record of what phone number called you and you may be able to trace him down.  Assuming he is a teenager, he likely has parents who would not be too pleased to learn what he does as a hobby.  I would go through your phone records and see if there is any way to track him down (I bet there is).  If you are able to track him down, I would try calling him or writing a letter to his parents.  Of course, it will be hard to prove he did anything as it will be he said/she said.<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts.<br>
