<br>
It *is* against the rules of this message board to offer cross-server trades here though, but that was a decision made by the Administrators of the board, and in no way reflects the opinions of SOE on the matter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teapray>Teapray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/22/03 1:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3919.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~abenlen/yawn.JPG height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warning about Dirfrops - and a lesson for all</span><hr size=1> If someone is willing to rip someone else of then they are willing to be a thief.  This time is was on a cross server trade.  Next time, it might be a horse.   <p>-- <br>
